<p><strong>Smile Orange: Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</strong></p>
<p><strong>What is Smile Orange?</strong></p>
<p>Smile Orange is a non-profit organization dedicated to providing affordable dental care to underserved communities. Founded in 2006, Smile Orange operates mobile dental clinics that offer a wide range of services, including cleanings, fillings, and extractions.</p>
<p><strong>How can I get an appointment with Smile Orange?</strong></p>
<p>To schedule an appointment with Smile Orange, you can call their toll-free number at <strong>[Phone Number]</strong>. You will need to provide basic information about yourself and your dental needs. Appointments are available at various locations on a rotating basis.</p>
<p><strong>What services does Smile Orange offer?</strong></p>
<p>Smile Orange provides a comprehensive range of dental services, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cleanings</li>
<li>Fillings</li>
<li>Extractions</li>
<li>X-rays</li>
<li>Sealants</li>
<li>Fluoride treatments</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>How much does it cost to visit Smile Orange?</strong></p>
<p>Smile Orange offers a sliding fee scale based on income. Patients without dental insurance can expect to pay between <strong>[$50-$200]</strong>. Those with dental insurance will typically only pay their co-pay.</p>
<p><strong>Can I volunteer with Smile Orange?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, Smile Orange welcomes volunteers of all ages and backgrounds. Volunteers can assist with tasks such as patient registration, dental hygiene, and community outreach. To learn more about volunteering, visit the Smile Orange website at <strong>[Website Address]</strong> or call <strong>[Phone Number]</strong>.</p>